  To enable MIDI, be sure computer's internal serial port is properly
  connected to a MIDI Interface. To play a sample via MIDI, edit the
  song in the tracker and set sample number to proper MIDI channel you
  want it to be played at.

  Example: Cm7 chord at MIDI channel 1


  22  --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000
  23  C-4 01 0000 0000 D#4 01 0000 0000 G-4 01 0000 0000 A#4 01 0000 0000
  24  --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000 --- 00 0000 0000

  Here all of the above 4 channels sends their data to MIDI channel 1.
  
  @{b}IMPORTANT!!!@{ub}

  Confusion can rise in the EDIT DATA window of the tracker. When you
  enable MIDI channels in this window they are named MIDI 01 to MIDI 16.
  Remember this has nothing to do with which channel they're playing
  later on, it's due to cybertracker keeping track on what's happening
  in each channel. So when you're setting up a song with MIDI enabled,
  every channel mapped to a MIDI channel can play MIDI channel 01 to 16.

  iieee... get it?   


